GlbList_A_Unval [String]   - Global-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of all unvalidated
                             files.

List_NS_All [Sig]          - File-list, unsorted, of all files in Sig.

List_NS_New [Sig]          - File-list, unsorted, of new files in Sig.

List_NS_Search [String]    - File-list, unsorted, of all files matching
                             string.

List_NS_SearchUL [Name]    - File-list, unsorted, of all files that
                             Name has uploaded.

List_NS_Unval [String]     - File-list, unsorted, of all unvalidated
                             files.

List_ON_All [Sig]          - File-list, sorted old->new, of all files
                             in Sig.

List_ON_New [Sig]          - File-list, sorted old->new, of new files
                             in Sig.

List_ON_Search [String]    - File-list, sorted old->new, of all files
                             matching string.

List_ON_SearchUL [Name]    - File-list, sorted old->new, of all files
                             that Name has uploaded.

List_ON_Unval [String]     - File-list, sorted old->new, of all unvalidated
                             files.

List_NO_All [Sig]          - File-list, sorted new->old, of all files
                             in Sig.

List_NO_New [Sig]          - File-list, sorted new->old, of new files
                             in Sig.

List_NO_Search [String]    - File-list, sorted new->old, of all files
                             matching string.

List_NO_SearchUL [Name]    - File-list, sorted new->old, of all files
                             that Name has uploaded.

List_NO_Unval [String]     - File-list, sorted new->old, of all unvalidated
                             files.

List_A_All [Sig]           - File-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of all files
                             in Sig.

List_A_New [Sig]           - File-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of new files
                             in Sig.

List_A_Search [String]     - File-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of all files
                             matching string.

List_A_SearchUL [Name]     - File-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of all files
                             that Name has uploaded.

List_A_Unval [String]      - File-list, sorted in alphabetic order, of all unvalidated
                             files.

ARexx <Filename>           - Executes an ARexx-script.

FPLHook <Functionname>     - Calls a Fpl-hook. The arg should be the function-
                             name, without (); Currently it's not possible
                             to pass arguments.

SimpleDOS <command>        - Executes a DOS command in a very simple way.
                             All output comes at once, and no userinput
                             is possible. Fast and safe.

SetNodeStatus <string>     - Sets current node's status in ReccControl and
                             in Who-programs.

RunFPL <filename>          - Executes a fpl-script

DOSDoor <filename>         - Runs a DOS-Door or a DOS-Command. Full IO.

Birthday                   - Checks if a user is having his birthday, and if,
                             displays the file Birthday.TXT

TogMsgTag [area]           - Toggles whether or not a msgarea should be scanned
                             during global new (Also affects waitingmail, IE, when
                             a untagged area recieves mail for you, it doesn't
                             notify you)
                             If [area] is ON every area is tagged
                             If [area] is OFF every area is untagged

TogFileTag [area]          - Toggles whether or not a filearea should be scanned
                             during global new.
                             If [area] is ON every area is tagged
                             If [area] is OFF every area is untagged

Brodcast <node> <text>     - Displays <text> on node <node>. BUt if <node> is ALL
                             instead of a number, it displays <text> on EVERY node
                             which is online in the system.

Compiler directives:
--------------------

MenuPage <Pagenr>    - The following is menupage X
EndMenu              - End of menupage.
HelpFile <textfile>  - Set helpfile for this menupage.
Prompt <textfile>    - Set prompt filename for this menupage.
Function <Character> - The following is what is going to happend when a user
                       press this key.
MinAccess <Level>    - Set minumum accesslevel for the following menucommands.
MaxAccess <Level>    - Set maximum accesslevel for the following menucommands.

@endnode

@node FPL "FPL commands"

Reccoon's unique FPL interface, allows the BBS to be completely customized.
Not only do you have all the FPL C commands, but you also have specific rcn
commands at your disposal.

All the @{"menu commands" Link Menu} are available, just put the arguments inside the ().
IE, if you were to use "Echo" which takes a string as an argument, you would
write this:

Echo("Hello World");

If the command don't have any arguments, just leave the () empty.
IE, if you where to use the Cls command, you would write this:

Cls();

NOTE! All FPL commands are CaSeSeNsItIvE and requires a semicolon at the end
      of the command.

@{"FPL only commands" Link FPLcmd}
@{"Advanced FPL" Link FPLadv}
@{"FPL hooks" Link FPLhook}

@endnode

@node FPLcmd "FPL-only commands:"

 Results:
   S = String
   I = Integer
   B = Boolean integer, 1 if success, 0 if less successful
 Args:
   i = Optional integer
   I = Req. integer
   s = Optional string
   S = Req. string

The FPL-script must for the moment be named RcnMenus.FPL and should
be located in your standard menu-drawer.

Note:  The fpl-menus are still under development, and therefore some
       fpl-commands are undocumented.

S = GetMenuKey(i showprompt)    - Get keyhit. If a nonzero value is passed,
                                  the prompt will be displayed.
B = SetMenuFile(S filename)     - File that will be displayed on ShowMenu()
B = SetPromptFile(S filename)   - Set promptfile
I = SetMenuNum(I page)          - Current menupage
I = GetMenuNum()                - Get current menupage
I = GetLevel()                  - Get user's accesslevel
I = GetGfx()                    - Get user's graphicsmode
S = GetName()                   - Get user's name
S = GetHandle()                 - Get user's handle
I = GetMsgSIG()                 - Get current message-SIG
I = GetMsgArea()                - Get current message-area
I = GetFileSIG()                - Get current file-SIG
I = GetFileArea()               - Get current file-area
I = GetAge()                    - Get user's age
I = GetULB()                    - Get user's upload-bytes statistic
I = GetULF()                    - Get user's upload-file statistic
I = GetDLB()                    - Get user's download-bytes statistic
I = GetDLF()                    - Get user's download-file statistic
I = GetBaud()                   - Get current baudrate (dtr<->modem)
I = GetBps()                    - Get current bpsrate (modem<->modem)
S = GetString(I len, i flags)   - Get a string from the user. Look at
                                  include/reccoon/reccoon.h for GS_ flags!
I = GetTimeUsed()               - Get how much time the user have been online
                                  this call.
I = GetTimeLeft()               - How much time the user has remaining.
I = AddTime(I minutes)          - Add Time to the user. This function
                                  returns how many minutes that was actually
                                  added. (a systemevent has high priority)
I = GetLine()                   - Current Reccoon-Line
B = YesNo(S prompt, i ykey, i nkey) - Prompt user for Yes or No. Defaults
                                  to YES.
B = NoYes(S prompt, i ykey, i nkey) - Prompt user for Yes or No. Defaults
                                  to NO.
S = CookString(S string )       - Converts Rcn displaycodes to a string that
                                  you can use in your program.


All normal menucommands returns B if called from FPL.

/* Fun and maybe useful example: */
   if(GetULB()>1000000 && GetLevel()<20) PRM_Access(20);
@endnode
@node FPLadv "Advanced FPL"

ANSI-C functions:
-----------------

Reccoon now supports a few io-commands accessable from fpl.
They're supposed to look as much like the ANSI-C commands as possible, but
since fpl lacks pointer-abilities, some commands are a little different.


int handle = fopen  (string filename, string accessmode);
                      Open file for reading or writing. Accessmode is a string
                     containing "r" for reading or "w" for writing. Consult a
                     C-manual for closer details.

void         fclose (int handle);
                      Closes a file opened by fopen()

string str = fgets  (int handle);
                      Reads a textline from a file. Newline-character will
                     be stripped. You must use feof() before you call this
                     function.

int error  = fputs  (string text, int handle);
                      Writes a string to a file.

int result = feof   (int handle);
                      Returns TRUE if current position in file is at the end
                     of the file. You must use this before any call to fgets
                     or any other future read-function.

int len    = printf (string string, arg1...);
                      Sends text to the user with % formatting.
                     %s  - String
                     %ld - Int (decimal)
                     %lu - Unsigned int (decimal)
                     %lx - Int (hex)
                     %lc - Chars
                     %%  - % sign
                     Note that you MUST use %ld instead of %d.


There is one important thing you must keep in mind: When using the
fgets() function (or any other readfunction that will be available in the
future), you must use the feof() function BEFORE the actual fgets().
That's because fpl can't receive a NULL-string as a result from Rcn.
This will not be necessary in future versions of Fpl where pointers
ARE supported.

Example:

void ShowAFile(string filename)
{
int handle;
string text;

   handle=fopen(filename,"r");
   if(handle){
      while(!feof(handle)){
         text=fgets(handle);
         Send(text);
         Send("\\n\\r");
      }
      fclose(handle);
   }
}

@endnode
@node FPLhook "FPL-Hooks:"

A 'Hook' is a function that will be called when Reccoon does something
special. A good example is the hook ArcViewer. That function will always
be called when the user selects View Archive at any time. They're there
so you can customize the BBS even more.

All FPL-Hooks must be located in the files RcnHooks.FPL in your menu-
directory. All functions must be prototyped to work.



int ArcViewer(string filename) - Called when the users selects ViewArchive.
                                 Return 0 if you don't want to call the
                                          ordinary archive-viewer
                                        1 to continue as normal.

int ArcTester(string filename) - Called when the users selects TestArchive.
                                 Return 0 if you don't want to call the
                                          ordinary archive-tester
                                        1 to continue as normal.

void XprFirst(string filename) - Called when xpr.library got it's first
                                 filename. Called once per download.

void XprNext(string filename)  - Called when xpr.library got it's next
                                 filename. Called one time per file
                                 in batch transfer.

int LogHook(string logtext)    - Called when Reccoon is trying to write
                                 something in the logfile.
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 if you want to abort the operation.

void MsgCreated(string toname) - Called right after an user has written a
                                 message.

void FileUploaded(string name) - Called when a file has been successfully
                                 copied to it's filearea. No path supplied.

void FileAttached(string name) - Called when a user has attached a file
                                 to a message. No path supplied.

int FileCopy(string fullname)  - Called right before a file is copied
                                 into a filearea. At this point you can add
                                 BBS-adds to the archive if you want to.
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 if you don't want the file to be
                                          copied.

int FileCopied(string fullname)- Called right after a file is successfully
                                 copied into a filearea.
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 if you don't want the file to be
                                          uploaded by Rcn. At this point you
                                          can start a door that looks for
                                          FILE_ID.DIZ and stuff like that.

                                 Be aware that this functions won't be called
                                 if FileCopy fails.

int ChatEngaged(void)          - Called when you break in for a chat.
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 if you DON'T want Rcn to enter
                                          chatmode. This makes it possible to
                                          replace Rcn's built in chat.

void ChatDisabled(void)        - Called when you exit chatmode.

int NewUser(void)              - Called right before all newuser-questions.
                                 Return -1 if you want Rcn to ask all
                                           questions as normal.
                                         0 if you don't want to add this
                                           user to the userfile
                                         1 if you want to add the user.

int Birthday(void)             - Called when a users is having his birthday
                                 allowing you to do something special =)
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 if you DONT want reccoon to show
                                          the Birthday.TXT.

int Front(void)                - Called just before the display of Welcome.
                                 Return 0 to continue as normal
                                        1 to logout
                                        2 to continue but NOT display Welcome

Want more hooks? Tell me where!
@endnode
